{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A request whose signature does not match its body is rejected with a 401 response; the body is not forwarded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is at a module handoff: HTTP handler + signature verifier + enqueue path. A unit test of HMAC comparison alone misses bugs where invalid requests still reach enqueue due to wiring/order mistakes. Not System: this can be reproduced with in-process request simulation and an in-memory spy queue; no real network/OS/subprocess is required. Not Agentic/Workflow: no AI/ML step.","test_description":"Run the handler with an in-process HTTP test harness, send a body with an intentionally wrong `X-Signature-256`, assert `401`, and assert queue `enqueue` is never called (or queue storage remains unchanged).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"An event is written to the persistent queue before the HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned to the sender.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is ordering across modules: handler ack timing versus real persistent-queue write completion. A pure unit test cannot catch ack-before-persist races. Use real queue module with its local persistence backend to verify ordering invariant. Not System: no real external network/subprocess is required if queue persistence is local to process/test environment. Not Agentic/Workflow: no model decisions.","test_description":"With the real queue implementation (backed by test-local persistence), inject a controllable delay around commit/append and assert `200` is observed only after durable write success signal; if write fails, assert no `200`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The handler returns the HTTP response without waiting for downstream processing of the event to finish.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is async decoupling between handler and downstream worker module. Unit tests on one function miss interaction bugs where handler accidentally awaits processing. Not System: in-process harness plus a downstream stub/promise is sufficient; no OS/network primitive needed. Not Agentic/Workflow: no AI steps.","test_description":"Wire handler to a downstream processor that blocks (e.g., unresolved promise for several seconds). Send a valid event and assert response is returned quickly while processor is still running, then later complete processor.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The response arrives within 3 seconds wall-clock time even when downstream processing of earlier events is slow and concurrent.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real-time/concurrency SLA under load; event-loop contention and scheduling effects are OS/runtime behaviors that mocks often hide. MOCK-HIDE applies: fake timing or single-threaded stubs can pass while real concurrent requests miss 3s. Not Agentic/Workflow: no AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"Start the service process, drive concurrent real HTTP requests while earlier events trigger intentionally slow downstream work, and measure end-to-end wall-clock latency of new requests; assert responses stay <3s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"An event whose ID was already received is not written to the queue a second time.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is in dedupe state handoff (ID tracking + queue write). Unit logic tests miss duplicate acceptance caused by repository/queue interaction or transaction ordering. Not System: can be caught with in-process modules and local persistence. Not Agentic/Workflow: no model output dependency.","test_description":"Submit the same event ID twice through the handler using real dedupe storage + real queue module in test environment; assert first request writes once and second does not add another queued record.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.77,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the queue reports it is full, the handler returns 503 with a Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is error-contract mapping across modules: queue-full signal to HTTP status/header. Unit tests of formatter miss integration bugs in propagation or mapping. Not System: no real network/subprocess required; in-process handler + real/controlled queue-full response is enough. Not Agentic/Workflow: no AI.","test_description":"Configure queue module (or test instance) to return a concrete `FULL` condition, send a valid request, and assert HTTP `503` plus `Retry-After` header value policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The persistent queue actually enforces its configured capacity limit and rejects events that would exceed it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This validates real queue implementation with persistence and capacity accounting; mocking would hide true enforcement bugs. Minimum is integration with actual queue module + real local storage backend. Higher-level System was considered, but behavior text does not require external network service or subprocess queue broker; if queue is local module, Integration is sufficient.","test_description":"Instantiate the real persistent queue against test-local storage with a small capacity, enqueue up to limit, then enqueue one more and assert deterministic rejection and unchanged persisted depth.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
